clone, copy config.example.js to config.js and fill in some details then

  npm install -g .

Now you can generate a token with

  chatkit-token '{ "userId": "alice", "su": true }'

All options supported by @pusher/chatkit-server are supported, argument is
JSON.

Good for curls

  curl https://us1.pusherplatform.io/services/chatkit/v1/$instance_id/users \
  -X SUBSCRIBE \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $(chatkit-token '{ "userId": "bob" }')"
